(186, '171', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', 'umoh ekpo Umoh', '0000-00-00', '2026-01-29 10:53:14', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(187, '172', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'presented with a history of recurrent headaches consistent with migraine. The headaches began approximately 3 days ago, The pain is typically insidious in onset, bilateral, and described as  throbbing. The intensity is moderate to severe and is aggravated by routine physical activity. Each episode lasts approximately 4 hours to 3 days if untreated.\nThe headaches are commonly associated with nausea and/or vomiting, photophobia, and phonophobia. The patient reports presence of aura, characterized by visual scintillations, zigzag lines, sensory disturbances occurring 5 minutes prior to headache onset.\nIdentified triggers include stress, lack of sleep, fasting, certain foods, hormonal changes). Relief is partially with rest, dark room, analgesics, triptans.\n\nThere is no history of fever, head trauma, seizures, focal neurological deficits, or altered consciousness. The patient denies red-flag symptoms such as sudden onset “thunderclap” headache, progressive worsening, or headaches associated with systemic illness.\n\nPast medical history is significant for Migraine. There is a positive family history of migraine. The patient is currently taking PCM and has no known drug allergies.', NULL, NULL, 'Migraine with aura', 'Neuroimaging (MRI brain)', '', 'DR. SEUN OLAIYA', '0000-00-00', '2026-01-29 12:44:37', 'Vital signs are within normal limits. The patient appears uncomfortable and prefers a quiet, dark environment.\n\nHead and neck examination reveals no scalp tenderness or temporal artery abnormalities. There is no neck stiffness or meningismus.\n\nNeurological examination is normal. Cranial nerves II–XII are intact. Motor strength is 5/5 in all extremities with normal tone and bulk. Sensory examination is intact. Deep tendon reflexes are 2+ and symmetric. Coordination and gait are normal.\n\nFundoscopic examination shows no papilledema. No focal neurological deficits are noted.\n\nCardiovascular, respiratory, and abdominal examinations are unremarkable.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
